        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We keep here the complete set-up identical to the other two sources of our proposal in order to allow for a best comparison of our three targets.

We aim to reach a flux limit of 50 microJy in band 7, which is best suited for our purpose with respect to sensitivity and wavelength range.

We ask for the best angular resolution in band 7 (maximum baseline) in order to obtain the best possible  astrometric accuracy for detected sources. There is no need for ACA, even though the object is not a point source. So, our time estimate is based on the assumption of a point source.

To achive 50 microJy in band 7 in dual polarization mode, ALMA's exposure time calculator predicts for this source in subband 1 at 336.5 GHz 19.31 min on target and 58.37 min in total, assuming standard weather conditions and 0.125 arcsec resolution (the minimum value that is accepted). No ACA time is requested. 

Adding together all our three targets, in total we request 169.72 min = 2.83 hrs telescope time.</prj:justificationText>
